Bullard ended up losing thousands in the fund, with Scotland Yard confirming that they are investigating fraud allegations made in February but that no arrests had been made.

The developments show why Bullard was willing to take ITV up on their offer, according to a source close to the 33-year-old.

‘The money isn’t normally anywhere near enough for Premier League footballers,’ they said.

‘Losing so much cash explains why he was keen to go.’

